HEADWORD: Tonsilotomy
<hw>Ton`sil*ot"o*my</hw> <pr>(?)</pr>, <pos>n.</pos> <fld>(Surg.)</fld>
<def>The operation of removing the tonsils, or a portion thereof; --
called more commonly <altname>tonsillectomy</altname>.</def>⟦br⟧
[<source>1913 Webster</source>]</p>

